To enhance the EACH_PATTERN regex and improve the processEachBlocks method, we can take the following steps:

1. Update the EACH_PATTERN to capture the entire <each> block, including its opening and closing tags:

```java
private static final Pattern EACH_PATTERN = Pattern.compile("<each\\s+items=\"\\$\\{([^}]+)}\">(.*?)</each>", Pattern.DOTALL);
```

2. Modify the processEachBlocks method to handle the complete block structure:

```java
private String processEachBlocks(String template, Map<String, Object> context) {
    Matcher matcher = EACH_PATTERN.matcher(template);
    StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer();
    while (matcher.find()) {
        String itemsVar = matcher.group(1);
        String blockContent = matcher.group(2);
        List<?> items = (List<?>) context.get(itemsVar);

        StringBuilder replacement = new StringBuilder();
        if (items != null) {
            for (Object item : items) {
                String processedContent = blockContent.replace("$[item]", item.toString());
                replacement.append(processedContent);
            }
        }

        matcher.appendReplacement(sb, Matcher.quoteReplacement(replacement.toString()));
    }
    matcher.appendTail(sb);
    return sb.toString();
}
```

These changes will ensure that the entire <each> block is processed correctly, removing the opening and closing tags while properly iterating over the items and replacing the placeholders.

