1. Update the EACH_PATTERN in the Template class to correctly capture the items attribute:
   ```java
   private static final Pattern EACH_PATTERN = Pattern.compile("<each\\s+items=\"\\$\\{([^}]+)}\">(.*?)</each>", Pattern.DOTALL);
   ```

2. Modify the processEachBlocks method to handle the items as a List:
   ```java
   private String processEachBlocks(String template, Map<String, Object> context) {
       Matcher matcher = EACH_PATTERN.matcher(template);
       StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer();
       while (matcher.find()) {
           String itemsVar = matcher.group(1);
           String blockContent = matcher.group(2);
           List<?> items = (List<?>) context.get(itemsVar);

           StringBuilder replacement = new StringBuilder();
           if (items != null && !items.isEmpty()) {
               for (Object item : items) {
                   replacement.append(processEachBlockItems(blockContent, item.toString()));
               }
           }
           matcher.appendReplacement(sb, Matcher.quoteReplacement(replacement.toString()));
       }
       matcher.appendTail(sb);
       return sb.toString();
   }
   ```

3. Update the render method to call processEachBlocks with the context:
   ```java
   public String render(String templatePath, Map<String, Object> context) {
       String template = readFile(templatePath);
       String result = replaceVariables(template, context);
       result = processEachBlocks(result, context);
       return result;
   }
   ```

These changes will correctly handle the `<each>` blocks, properly iterating over the lists provided in the context and replacing the `$[item]` placeholders with the correct values.
